activists were thronging to the nations 
capital today for a demonstration that organizers hope will cement 
public opinion once and for all in favor of a womans right to an 
abortion 
march leaders say the demonstration on sunday will launch a 
campaign that includes nationwide distribution of a videotape aimed 
at countering the antiabortion movements trademark video 
silent scream 
the 20minute videotape abortion for survival includes 
footage of a woman undergoing an abortion to show the procedure is 
safe and simple and the indiscernible remains taken from the 
uterus in a firsttrimester abortion 
the videotape puts it where its at said eleanor smeal 
president of the fund for the feminist majority it talks about 
abortion as a public health necessity and essential for the 
wellbeing of millions of american women 
it features the central issue of this debate what is 
abortion why its needed and why the public health and medical 
establishment of our society and worldwide is for keeping it 
legal 
the tape is being distributed to government officials and 
members of congress and state legislatures as well as on college 
campuses nationwide she said 
silent scream expresses the antiabortion view by depicting 
a fetus being aborted 
march organizers said other parts of their campaign include 
applying pressure on government agencies and pharmaceutical 
companies to improve available contraception and standing up to 
operation rescues attempts to close down abortion clinics 
the march is aimed at womens rights in general and a pending 
supreme court decision that could reverse its 1973 landmark ruling 
roe vs wade which legalized abortion oral arguments in the new 
case are scheduled for april 26 
president bush told antiabortion activists a few days after he 
moved into the oval office that he wanted the decision overturned 
bush faced white house reporters on friday but was not asked 
about the march or his views on abortion at a news conference that 
covered issues ranging from the irancontra affair to the minimum 
wage the alaska oil spill to foreign policy in the middle east and 
the soviet union 
march organizers said students were coming from about 500 
college campuses many of them in the northeast where many college 
students are within easy traveling distance of washington 
other delegations of students as well as activists representing 
churches labor unions and other groups across the country are 
coming dozens of celebrities are also scheduled to appear 
molly yard president of the national organization for women 
said she expected the size of the demonstration will be easily 
double and probably be considerably larger than the 
washington march three years ago which drew a crowd police 
estimated at 90000 
a counterdemonstration by antiabortion advocates is expected to 
draw about 300 people during sundays prochoice march from the 
washington monument down the mall to the capitol 
