no one in the us government learned before 1986 that hawk 
missiles had been shipped to iran in november 1985 
north testified that although he was at a meeting nov 20 1986 
where congressional testimony was discussed he played no part in 
shaping prepared testimony 
according to the evidence those receiving summaries of such 
intercepts included national security adviser robert mcfarlane or 
north and cia director william casey or his deputy also receiving 
them were defense secretary caspar weinberger and the chairman of 
the joint chiefs of staff john vessey and his deputy 
casey sat in on the nov 20 1986 meeting which was intended to 
prepare him and national security adviser john poindexter for 
congressional appearances on the iran initiative the next day 
according to testimony 
the cia participants brought to the meeting a proposed insert 
saying the spy agency had been told the shipment was oil drilling 
equipment 
the cia had arranged at norths request to have one of its 
airlines transport the hawks in 1985 but did so without first 
getting a presidential finding 
north recalled that as the irancontra affair unfolded in 
november 1986 he spoke to his former boss mcfarlane about the 
shipment of hawks 
mcfarlane said that it didnt happen north said 
you knew it happened asked sullivan 
yes sir replied north he called me up from europe and 
made it happen 
in testimony during norths trial mcfarlane had a different 
recollection mcfarlane said north told him that he believed he 
and i hadnt learned the precise details of what happened until 
12 months after the shipment 
mcfarlane said he doubted at the time of the 1986 conversation 
that north was correct but that his own memory of the 1985 
shipment was hazy so that he couldnt contradict north 
as a result mcfarlane said he changed a chronology of the iran 
arms shipments removing a reference to the november 1985 shipment 
of hawks and substituting instead a more general reference to other 
transfers of equipment 
