that estimates of about 12 fatalities from the sinking friday of 
the soviet mike class submarine appeared accurate some crewmen 
apparently were rescued holst said but he provided no details 
a norwegian orion reconnaissance plane saw soviet ships and 
planes circling the accident site north of the arctic circle before 
nightfall friday a second orion passed over the area after 
midnight and spotted an oil slick on the sea holst said 
he said a soviet cruiser was en route to the scene and that 
norwegian vessels had made no attempts to approach the site 118 
miles southsouthwest of bear island in the norwegian sea and 312 
miles off norway 
