peter v ueberroths 464 million deal to buy 
eastern airlines and share ownership with its unions is a major 
step toward untangling the strikebound carriers problems 
but can ueberroth and his team or another potential suitor who 
might emerge resurrect eastern as a competitive airline 
once any buyer gets the company back into operation easterns 
new managers will have to repair its battered service reputation 
regain customers who deserted the virtually grounded airline and 
compete headon with such aggressive rivals as delta air lines and 
american airlines that already have muscled further into eastern 
turf 
cheaper fares at least for the first few weeks eastern is back 
into the air are a strong possibility to lure back passengers 
observers believe 
